2
00:00:02,580 --> 00:00:04,820
All characters, behaviours, settings, and events depicted in this drama are entirely fictitious.

3
00:00:04,820 --> 00:00:06,660
They are not designed to allude to any particular entity, occupation, or group of people.

4
00:00:06,660 --> 00:00:09,980
Viewer discretion is advised.

5
00:00:10,020 --> 00:00:13,110
[North Star Entertainment]

6
00:00:13,110 --> 00:00:14,980
[IQIYI]

7
00:00:15,150 --> 00:00:17,180
[Present]

8
00:00:19,550 --> 00:00:26,510
♫Never met anyone who could make me understand this word♫

9
00:00:27,880 --> 00:00:34,780
♫But when I met you, my heart started beating fast♫

10
00:00:36,010 --> 00:00:43,180
♫You’re the only one in my heart who could make me feel this way♫

11
00:00:44,380 --> 00:00:50,910
♫This long-awaitied moment is now over♫

12
00:00:52,080 --> 00:00:56,350
♫From now on, my heart and soul will be yours for the rest of my life♫

13
00:00:56,350 --> 00:00:59,680
♫Always have each other, never let go♫

14
00:01:00,050 --> 00:01:04,750
♫Trust in me ‘cause I’ll be by your side♫

15
00:01:04,750 --> 00:01:09,780
♫Hold my hand, Baby♫

16
00:01:09,780 --> 00:01:12,980
[Desires in the Wind]

17
00:01:13,390 --> 00:01:17,810
[Previously]
Does Wind have a girlfriend or anyone she likes yet? If so, I’ll back off.

18
00:01:17,810 --> 00:01:20,390
Traitors! I’ll have you all executed!

19
00:01:20,860 --> 00:01:23,060
Last night, I just got drunk and fell asleep…

20
00:01:23,060 --> 00:01:25,140
and didn’t do anything weird, did I?

21
00:01:25,300 --> 00:01:26,660
You fell asleep right away.

22
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:28,900
Don't you go sweet talking like this to anyone.

23
00:01:29,330 --> 00:01:32,470
They might misunderstand and get the wrong idea.

24
00:01:32,600 --> 00:01:35,560
Do you really not know who it is that Wind likes?

25
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:38,930
The person Wind likes is you.

26
00:01:39,360 --> 00:01:42,530
If you don’t believe me, just go ask Wind yourself.

27
00:01:43,530 --> 00:01:45,460
Everything will be over soon.

28
00:01:45,930 --> 00:01:48,660
And I’ll take you back to Madelin myself.

29
00:02:00,200 --> 00:02:02,260
Do you need anything?

30
00:02:05,060 --> 00:02:08,020
Ask Bua too. Does she need anything?

31
00:02:08,020 --> 00:02:11,890
She’ll give me an earful if I forget to buy it for her. That rascal.

32
00:02:14,180 --> 00:02:16,100
Just call me if you need anything.

33
00:02:18,310 --> 00:02:19,810
Okay, sure.

34
00:03:24,930 --> 00:03:26,860
Bua will take you out today.

35
00:03:26,860 --> 00:03:28,460
I can’t go with you.

36
00:03:28,700 --> 00:03:30,680
I have to look after the house for Uncle Boonsong.

37
00:03:31,850 --> 00:03:32,560
Mhm.

38
00:03:37,200 --> 00:03:41,140
What are you writing?

39
00:03:50,760 --> 00:03:52,300
Isn’t this the Madelin language?

40
00:03:54,860 --> 00:03:59,850
If you ever see this message, run away immediately.

41
00:04:01,100 --> 00:04:03,060
I have a boat ready at the back of the bay.

42
00:04:07,900 --> 00:04:10,390
You want me to run? What about you?

43
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:13,720
I’ll be right after.

44
00:04:14,730 --> 00:04:16,529
I won’t let you go alone.

45
00:04:21,529 --> 00:04:23,360
Why mention this all of a sudden?

46
00:04:25,400 --> 00:04:28,390
It’s just in case.

47
00:04:55,020 --> 00:04:59,100
Hey, just want to let you know I caught lots of fish last night.

48
00:04:59,770 --> 00:05:02,720
Get ready for a feast, honey.

49
00:05:11,860 --> 00:05:12,900
What do you want?

50
00:05:13,300 --> 00:05:15,000
I don’t have anything valuable on me.

51
00:05:15,160 --> 00:05:18,060
Shut up. Take me to your boat.

52
00:05:18,730 --> 00:05:19,970
Move!

53
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:37,270
Take me to the princess and I’ll spare your life.

54
00:05:39,390 --> 00:05:41,060
I’m just an old fisherman.

55
00:05:41,060 --> 00:05:44,310
I have no idea what princess you’re looking for–

56
00:05:44,330 --> 00:05:48,140
If I dump your body in the sea, I doubt anyone would find it.

57
00:06:01,700 --> 00:06:03,300
See you on the island.

58
00:06:03,860 --> 00:06:05,130
I already got someone to take me there.

59
00:06:17,530 --> 00:06:19,600
Geez, Miss Phat.

60
00:06:19,600 --> 00:06:21,390
I still haven’t caught much.

61
00:06:21,390 --> 00:06:22,930
Why do we have to go back now?

62
00:06:23,560 --> 00:06:25,390
I’m not feeling quite well.

63
00:06:26,100 --> 00:06:29,100
Oh, you’re not feeling well?

64
00:06:29,360 --> 00:06:30,930
How are you feeling now?

65
00:06:31,460 --> 00:06:32,770
A bit exhausted from the sun.

66
00:06:33,760 --> 00:06:35,720
I’ll get you some pills then.

67
00:06:35,960 --> 00:06:37,200
Hurry up! Hurry up!

68
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:39,800
Move!

69
00:06:43,100 --> 00:06:43,800
Lead the way.

70
00:06:43,800 --> 00:06:45,600
Show us the way, you old coot!

71
00:06:54,500 --> 00:06:55,260
Where is she?

72
00:06:56,140 --> 00:06:57,310
Hang on.

73
00:06:59,430 --> 00:07:00,810
Hurry up.

74
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:05,960
You guys get ready.

75
00:07:07,700 --> 00:07:09,360
Split up and seach!

76
00:07:35,260 --> 00:07:37,060
Hey, found anyone?

77
00:07:37,560 --> 00:07:38,860
No, not a soul here.

78
00:07:40,560 --> 00:07:42,360
Where has everyone gone?

79
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:44,260
Are you f***ing with me?

80
00:07:44,730 --> 00:07:45,760
No…No, sir.

81
00:07:51,530 --> 00:07:55,270
There. That’s Vayo–the girl you’re looking for.

82
00:07:56,890 --> 00:08:00,430
Go get her and the princess! Go!

83
00:08:00,460 --> 00:08:01,260
Quick!

84
00:08:08,960 --> 00:08:10,200
Go, go , go!

85
00:08:10,730 --> 00:08:11,930
Comb the place!

86
00:08:14,700 --> 00:08:15,860
Split up! Now!

87
00:08:16,100 --> 00:08:19,390
Over there. That way. There too!

88
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:39,679
If you ever see this message, run away immediately.

89
00:08:39,679 --> 00:08:41,559
I have a boat ready at the back of the bay.

90
00:08:46,130 --> 00:08:46,930
Found them?

91
00:08:47,160 --> 00:08:48,270
No, Boss.

92
00:08:51,960 --> 00:08:52,760
It’s a trap!

93
00:09:10,400 --> 00:09:20,760
Shit, the cops! Run! Take cover!

94
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:28,310
Turn yourself in!

95
00:09:59,600 --> 00:10:05,100
F***ing bitch! Just you wait! Cover me, quick!

96
00:10:41,660 --> 00:10:42,890
Miss Blew!

97
00:10:44,930 --> 00:10:46,000
Miss Fai! How did you get here?

98
00:10:46,600 --> 00:10:49,140
Lom sent me to get you. We have to go now.

99
00:10:49,360 --> 00:10:51,520
What’s going on? Where’s Miss Vayo?

100
00:10:51,760 --> 00:10:55,390
Don’t worry about her. We have to take you to a safer place.

101
00:10:55,390 --> 00:10:56,890
They’ll be coming this way soon.

102
00:10:56,930 --> 00:11:00,130
But isn’t Miss Vayo in danger right now? We have to help her.

103
00:11:02,160 --> 00:11:05,270
Please trust my sister. Let’s get on a boat.

104
00:11:05,270 --> 00:11:07,970
It’s for your own safety. We have to get out of here as fast as we can.

105
00:11:12,500 --> 00:11:13,460
Let’s go!

106
00:11:14,800 --> 00:11:16,100
Hurry up, Miss Blew!

107
00:11:38,660 --> 00:11:41,430
She’s over there!

108
00:11:43,430 --> 00:11:46,430
Find a boat and go after them! Go!

109
00:12:14,260 --> 00:12:17,430
There! Go faster!

110
00:12:27,930 --> 00:12:28,900
They’re here.

111
00:12:30,470 --> 00:12:31,640
Miss Blew!

112
00:13:13,220 --> 00:13:14,720
F*** it!

113
00:13:17,100 --> 00:13:18,220
Uncle!

114
00:13:20,600 --> 00:13:23,970
Hey, go closer!

115
00:14:04,640 --> 00:14:05,850
Lom!

116
00:14:18,860 --> 00:14:20,470
Are you all right, Miss Blew?

117
00:14:26,360 --> 00:14:28,100
Look out, Vayo!

118
00:14:32,930 --> 00:14:33,730
Lom!

119
00:14:40,500 --> 00:14:41,330
Lom!

120
00:14:48,330 --> 00:14:49,600
Miss Blew!

121
00:15:02,200 --> 00:15:03,000
Lom!

122
00:15:04,100 --> 00:15:04,900
Lom!

123
00:15:08,860 --> 00:15:10,600
She’s wearing a ballistic vest.

124
00:15:17,260 --> 00:15:18,060
Lom.

125
00:15:23,560 --> 00:15:26,770
Miss Vayo, wake up.

126
00:15:57,460 --> 00:15:58,260
Lom!

127
00:15:58,640 --> 00:15:59,890
Miss Vayo.

128
00:16:33,060 --> 00:16:39,180
Miss Vayo, Miss Vayo.

129
00:16:47,600 --> 00:16:48,400
Miss Vayo.

130
00:16:50,730 --> 00:16:51,530
Miss Vayo.

131
00:16:52,800 --> 00:16:53,520
Lom!

132
00:16:53,930 --> 00:16:54,930
Miss Vayo.

133
00:17:04,130 --> 00:17:06,390
Don’t put yourself in danger like that,

134
00:17:06,530 --> 00:17:08,180
or conceal anything from me ever again.

135
00:17:08,640 --> 00:17:12,970
If anything happens to you, I’d blame myself for the rest of my life.

136
00:17:16,520 --> 00:17:18,390
I’m all right.

137
00:17:48,520 --> 00:17:52,020
[Boonwech Hospital]

138
00:18:07,500 --> 00:18:08,660
Hello, Uncle Wathit.

139
00:18:21,760 --> 00:18:23,330
Are you all right, Your Highness?

140
00:18:23,800 --> 00:18:28,760
I’m fine. Are Uncle Boonsong and everyone on the island all right?

141
00:18:29,600 --> 00:18:30,730
Yes, Your Highness.

142
00:18:39,600 --> 00:18:41,000
How is Lom, Your Highness?

143
00:18:43,860 --> 00:18:47,760
The doctor said she’s safe now. Nothing to worry about.

144
00:18:50,600 --> 00:18:57,130
Then, would you kindly grant me a private audience with you, Your Highness?

145
00:19:02,260 --> 00:19:04,330
I’ll look after Lom for you.

146
00:19:10,300 --> 00:19:11,770
Please, Your Highness.

147
00:19:26,360 --> 00:19:30,960
I must apologize for causing your daughter to be in great danger.

148
00:19:32,260 --> 00:19:34,200
It’s not your fault, Your Highness.

149
00:19:35,800 --> 00:19:38,000
It’s those traitors who are to be blamed.

150
00:19:39,930 --> 00:19:43,960
As for those attackers, they’re all taken care of, Your Highness.

151
00:19:45,300 --> 00:19:48,560
But I’m afraid…

152
00:19:50,930 --> 00:19:55,400
there might still be more of them.

153
00:19:56,600 --> 00:20:00,930
So, I’d like you to be more cautious, Your Highness.

154
00:20:04,960 --> 00:20:06,890
I’m well aware of the situation.

155
00:20:07,770 --> 00:20:12,640
But I’m afraid those traitors will never let me return to Madelin alive.

156
00:20:13,060 --> 00:20:15,100
Please don’t worry, Your Highness.

157
00:20:15,850 --> 00:20:19,680
Fah will soon be able to contact your people in Madelin.

158
00:20:20,660 --> 00:20:29,520
I awfully hope our plan will succeed before my imposter will conclude her visit and return to Madelin.

159
00:20:30,800 --> 00:20:36,470
I’m going to request for the list of individuals who are entering Thailand.

160
00:20:37,060 --> 00:20:41,720
Should any of them are from Madelin, I will inform you immediately, Your Highness.

161
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:45,730
I want it to be over as soon as possible.

162
00:20:47,100 --> 00:20:51,930
I don’t want Miss Vayo to risk her life for me any further.

163
00:21:18,810 --> 00:21:22,640
Aww, looking for your girl first thing when you’re awake, huh?

164
00:21:23,100 --> 00:21:26,560
Are you disappointed to see your little sister instead?

165
00:21:27,400 --> 00:21:28,350
Where’s Miss Blew?

166
00:21:29,390 --> 00:21:31,270
Outside, talking to Uncle Thit.

167
00:21:34,330 --> 00:21:35,680
Dad’s here?

168
00:21:35,930 --> 00:21:41,000
Yeah. But he’ll probably leave soon. He said he has a lot to take care of.

169
00:21:44,330 --> 00:21:46,500
How long do I have to stay here?

170
00:21:48,770 --> 00:21:53,100
No idea. But isn't it better to stay longer?

171
00:21:54,060 --> 00:21:56,470
So that you can act all clingy to Miss Blew.

172
00:21:58,760 --> 00:22:00,600
Watch it, give her some respect.

173
00:22:01,060 --> 00:22:05,520
Aww, acting all protective, huh, Lieutenant?

174
00:22:09,100 --> 00:22:11,350
There she is.

175
00:22:17,200 --> 00:22:19,850
Miss Vayo, how are you feeling?

176
00:22:21,100 --> 00:22:26,020
I’m good now. Thank you for saving me, Miss Blew.

177
00:22:26,760 --> 00:22:32,810
I was so scared when you got shot. Please don’t risk yourself like that again.

178
00:22:42,100 --> 00:22:43,770
Oh, Nam is here.

179
00:22:44,470 --> 00:22:47,930
Are you all right? I was shocked when I heard it.

180
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:51,400
I’m okay, Sis. Not a big deal at all.

181
00:22:51,760 --> 00:22:55,600
Not a big deal, my foot! You guys almost got yourself killed!

182
00:22:57,400 --> 00:22:59,470
And you even hid it from me and Din.

183
00:23:01,300 --> 00:23:03,600
Would you let me do it if I told you so?

184
00:23:03,900 --> 00:23:04,700
Lom!

185
00:23:07,060 --> 00:23:08,430
What is this about?

186
00:23:09,960 --> 00:23:11,100
I want to know too.

187
00:23:15,900 --> 00:23:20,100
Well, Dad and I set up a plan to lure those thugs out.

188
00:23:23,730 --> 00:23:27,890
I could sense I was being followed for quite a while back.

189
00:23:28,130 --> 00:23:31,810
We believe they’d soon find out about the island and come after us.

190
00:23:34,800 --> 00:23:37,100
So, we came up with a plan to get them.

191
00:23:37,130 --> 00:23:38,720
Your Stir-fried Squid with Basil, Miss.

192
00:23:52,730 --> 00:23:54,560
Your green tea is here, Young Master.

193
00:23:57,600 --> 00:24:00,270
Looks like you’re being followed.

194
00:24:01,130 --> 00:24:02,890
Yeah, for a while now.

195
00:24:02,900 --> 00:24:05,100
Tell our men to find out who they are.

196
00:24:05,360 --> 00:24:09,640
And tell Uncle Boon not to leave the island during this time. Not until I say anything.

197
00:24:09,700 --> 00:24:11,530
So, I had someone look into them.

198
00:24:15,300 --> 00:24:16,260
Yes, Uncle Yod?

199
00:24:16,560 --> 00:24:18,260
It’s as you thought, Young Master.

200
00:24:18,560 --> 00:24:20,000
They’re not from around here.

201
00:24:20,560 --> 00:24:23,000
They have a picture of Miss Lom and keep asking every villager if they’ve seen her.

202
00:24:23,930 --> 00:24:26,060
They’ve discovered our track.

203
00:24:26,260 --> 00:24:28,640
It won’t be long until they’ll find the island.

204
00:24:29,000 --> 00:24:31,270
Definitely the hitmen from Madelin.

205
00:24:31,600 --> 00:24:33,350
They’ve found us faster than I thought.

206
00:24:33,360 --> 00:24:34,900
What are you going to do then?

207
00:24:35,100 --> 00:24:36,720
Do you want to move somewhere else?

208
00:24:37,560 --> 00:24:41,850
No, I’ll come up with a plan to trap them.

209
00:24:42,730 --> 00:24:44,430
Can you contact Dad for me?

210
00:24:46,300 --> 00:24:48,330
Anyway, when are you leaving?

211
00:24:49,160 --> 00:24:50,930
Tomorrow morning, I guess.

212
00:24:51,300 --> 00:24:53,600
That’s your coffee. I ordered it for you.

213
00:24:54,600 --> 00:24:55,400
Thanks, dear.

214
00:24:55,560 --> 00:24:56,730
Drink something first, to freshen up.

215
00:24:57,160 --> 00:24:58,060
Yeah, it’s so hot today.

216
00:25:02,460 --> 00:25:03,520
How is it?

217
00:25:05,270 --> 00:25:06,260
Did they put galangal in there too?

218
00:25:06,460 --> 00:25:10,800
What galangal? Not a drop of sugar here–so strong I could stay up all night!

219
00:25:25,560 --> 00:25:27,730
Yes, Boss. I think I’ve found him.

220
00:25:32,900 --> 00:25:37,100
What a foul luck, he’s barking up the wrong tree. Wait till Young Master gets him.

221
00:25:38,960 --> 00:25:41,300
Yes, I’ll keep an eye on him.

222
00:25:59,400 --> 00:26:01,760
They’ve followed us here like you said, Uncle Thit.

223
00:26:02,130 --> 00:26:03,100
What now?

224
00:26:03,600 --> 00:26:05,660
I’ll send some men to standby on the island.

225
00:26:06,530 --> 00:26:08,200
Those thugs will definitely show up there tomorrow.

226
00:26:09,360 --> 00:26:11,100
I’ll go help Lom there too.

227
00:26:11,460 --> 00:26:13,000
Take care of yourself too, Fai.

228
00:26:13,460 --> 00:26:15,140
Can you put my team on the line?

229
00:26:15,140 --> 00:26:16,100
Hang on.

230
00:26:18,960 --> 00:26:19,760
Yes, sir.

231
00:26:22,800 --> 00:26:28,600
Hey, I caught lots of fish last night.

232
00:26:29,270 --> 00:26:32,310
Get ready for a feast, honey.

233
00:26:32,310 --> 00:26:34,560
Thank you, Uncle. Please be careful too.

234
00:26:37,900 --> 00:26:40,720
They’re coming. Let’s stick to our plan.

235
00:26:41,160 --> 00:26:42,520
What about Miss Blew?

236
00:26:42,520 --> 00:26:43,970
I already told Bua to keep watch.

237
00:26:44,330 --> 00:26:48,680
If Miss Blew hears the gunshot, she’ll probably run back to the cottage.

238
00:26:48,680 --> 00:26:50,900
Don’t worry, I already wrote a secret sign for her to run away.

239
00:26:51,160 --> 00:26:53,860
Please make sure you take her to the boat I’ve prepared.

240
00:26:54,130 --> 00:26:55,800
Just leave the rest to me.

241
00:26:56,660 --> 00:26:59,560
Okay, don’t worry. But please be careful.

242
00:27:08,360 --> 00:27:09,850
This is something serious.

243
00:27:09,930 --> 00:27:13,520
Shouldn’t any of you at least tell me about it?

244
00:27:13,660 --> 00:27:14,460
Fai?

245
00:27:18,260 --> 00:27:19,860
It’s not like I didn’t want to tell you.

246
00:27:20,300 --> 00:27:23,970
But it was quite a last-minute decision.

247
00:27:24,330 --> 00:27:26,430
I was the one who came up with the idea.

248
00:27:27,130 --> 00:27:28,460
Please don’t blame her.

249
00:27:29,200 --> 00:27:31,400
I told her not to tell anyone.

250
00:27:35,730 --> 00:27:37,130
My apologies, Miss Nam.

251
00:27:38,800 --> 00:27:40,850
It’s not your fault, Miss Blew.

252
00:27:42,260 --> 00:27:46,220
This is a matter of life and death, don’t you think you should at least let me know?

253
00:27:47,760 --> 00:27:52,270
I think there’s no use finding who’s at fault right now.

254
00:27:52,640 --> 00:27:55,180
Aren’t we lucky enough that everyone is safe?

255
00:27:55,640 --> 00:27:57,890
Yes, so lucky, right?

256
00:27:58,770 --> 00:28:00,060
Absolutely.

257
00:28:01,810 --> 00:28:04,970
We’re good now. Safe and sound.

258
00:28:05,470 --> 00:28:06,470
You brat.

259
00:28:08,100 --> 00:28:10,890
So, how are you feeling? Better?

260
00:28:11,000 --> 00:28:11,800
I’m good.

261
00:28:14,760 --> 00:28:16,300
Were you really going to keep quiet about it?

262
00:28:16,660 --> 00:28:17,860
She said ‘don’t tell anyone’.

263
00:28:54,530 --> 00:28:55,460
Please drink some water.

264
00:28:56,060 --> 00:28:57,000
Okay, Din.

265
00:28:58,530 --> 00:28:59,460
See you later.

266
00:29:04,760 --> 00:29:07,270
Din and Boss Rose are at the airport now.

267
00:29:07,270 --> 00:29:08,970
They’ll probably arrive here late at night.

268
00:29:08,970 --> 00:29:11,310
They’ll come visit you tomorrow.

269
00:29:11,930 --> 00:29:13,720
What’s with all the fuss?

270
00:29:13,720 --> 00:29:14,970
It’s nothing serious.

271
00:29:14,970 --> 00:29:16,850
I’ll be out of here soon.

272
00:29:17,660 --> 00:29:19,700
Be nice, Lom. They care about you.

273
00:29:33,000 --> 00:29:35,180
It’s been quite a day, isn’t it?

274
00:29:35,460 --> 00:29:36,800
Let’s go back and get some rest.

275
00:29:37,130 --> 00:29:38,600
Lom needs to rest too.

276
00:29:39,760 --> 00:29:42,060
You and Lada can stay at my place.

277
00:29:42,200 --> 00:29:43,600
I already told them to prepare a room for you.

278
00:29:48,060 --> 00:29:50,770
What about you, Miss Blew?

279
00:29:52,400 --> 00:29:54,560
I think I’m going to stay here with Miss Vayo.

280
00:29:56,260 --> 00:29:59,770
Why don’t you go back and get some rest first?

281
00:30:00,760 --> 00:30:03,720
There are cops guarding this room and keeping watch here anyway.

282
00:30:07,900 --> 00:30:10,060
She risked her life for me.

283
00:30:10,860 --> 00:30:14,140
If there’s anything I can do to repay her, I’m willing to do it.

284
00:30:15,960 --> 00:30:18,000
Please go home and get some rest first, Miss Blew.

285
00:30:18,260 --> 00:30:19,400
You’ll be more comfortable there.

286
00:30:20,300 --> 00:30:21,100
Don’t worry about me.

287
00:30:22,930 --> 00:30:27,560
Are you declining my offer to stay and trying to get rid of me?

288
00:30:28,730 --> 00:30:30,430
No, it’s not like that.

289
00:30:30,960 --> 00:30:32,600
I want you to stay.

290
00:30:34,860 --> 00:30:37,060
I’m just afraid you might feel uncomfortable.

291
00:30:39,060 --> 00:30:42,470
It doesn’t matter. I’ll never leave you.

292
00:30:53,760 --> 00:30:56,310
All right then. That’s settled.

293
00:30:56,600 --> 00:30:58,130
Come, let’s go home.

294
00:30:59,960 --> 00:31:01,470
We’re leaving, Sis.

295
00:31:02,060 --> 00:31:03,130
Get lots of rest.

296
00:31:03,700 --> 00:31:04,560
Please get well soon.

297
00:31:04,960 --> 00:31:05,760
Thank you.

298
00:31:06,360 --> 00:31:07,770
Get well soon.

299
00:31:08,330 --> 00:31:09,130
Thanks.

300
00:31:22,700 --> 00:31:23,560
Babe.

301
00:31:24,000 --> 00:31:24,560
Yes?

302
00:31:24,560 --> 00:31:27,960
About Miss Blew and Lom, do you also think the same as I do?

303
00:31:29,760 --> 00:31:30,800
What are you thinking?

304
00:31:31,730 --> 00:31:34,930
Well, something between them has changed.

305
00:31:34,930 --> 00:31:38,970
The way they look at each other is like when you look at someone you love.

306
00:31:41,800 --> 00:31:44,350
You probably imagined it.

307
00:31:44,660 --> 00:31:46,890
Lom should know best what is what.

308
00:31:48,800 --> 00:31:53,850
Haven’t you heard of a saying–‘nothing is impossible’?

309
00:31:54,860 --> 00:31:56,180
What do you mean?

310
00:31:57,560 --> 00:32:00,220
It’s better if you hear it from her yourself.

311
00:32:00,900 --> 00:32:01,930
The lift is here.

312
00:32:01,930 --> 00:32:03,390
Oh, come on.

313
00:32:03,800 --> 00:32:04,600
What have you got?

314
00:32:04,900 --> 00:32:05,700
Nothing.

315
00:32:05,800 --> 00:32:06,800
Spit it out right now.

316
00:32:07,100 --> 00:32:08,310
Give me 500 first.

317
00:32:09,200 --> 00:32:12,390
- Fai, tell me now.
- Really, you two.

318
00:32:12,400 --> 00:32:13,680
1,000 if you drag it longer.

319
00:32:19,360 --> 00:32:20,160
What did you say?

320
00:32:21,260 --> 00:32:24,060
Those you sent to kill Blew are all dead?

321
00:32:26,130 --> 00:32:27,900
All shot dead by the police.

322
00:32:30,160 --> 00:32:32,700
It’s definitely that cop and her father’s doing.

323
00:32:38,460 --> 00:32:42,350
Now what? We have to go back to Madelin soon.

324
00:32:42,350 --> 00:32:45,970
If that annoying princess is still alive, all of our efforts would be in vain.

325
00:32:46,100 --> 00:32:47,520
The nerve to ask me that.

326
00:32:47,520 --> 00:32:52,640
If you hadn’t hired those muppets and just taken care of this matter yourself,

327
00:32:52,640 --> 00:32:54,930
she would have been dead long ago!

328
00:32:55,600 --> 00:32:58,930
It’s you who must be responsible for this!

329
00:33:45,330 --> 00:33:46,500
Can’t sleep?

330
00:33:54,000 --> 00:33:56,100
Why are you still awake?

331
00:33:58,060 --> 00:34:00,860
I already slept a lot today. Don’t need any of it now.

332
00:34:01,460 --> 00:34:05,640
But you’re sick. You should sleep a lot so that you’ll recover soon.

333
00:34:12,400 --> 00:34:14,560
Why are you looking at me?

334
00:34:16,929 --> 00:34:18,060
I’m just glad.

335
00:34:20,960 --> 00:34:23,100
I’m glad you’re here.

336
00:34:30,460 --> 00:34:31,889
I need to get some sleep.

337
00:34:32,360 --> 00:34:33,600
Let’s talk tomorrow.

338
00:34:57,560 --> 00:34:59,860
I’ll never forget what you’ve kindly given me.

339
00:35:01,460 --> 00:35:03,600
I owe you my life, Miss blew.

340
00:35:06,900 --> 00:35:11,640
I don’t want anything in return for helping you.

341
00:35:12,860 --> 00:35:14,260
Get some sleep, Miss Vayo.

342
00:35:15,560 --> 00:35:23,560
I can’t. How can I sleep when my life savior is having a hard time sleeping on a sofa?

343
00:35:24,330 --> 00:35:27,800
I’m good here. I even slept on a fruit truck before, remember?

344
00:35:32,060 --> 00:35:34,270
I still don’t feel good about it.

345
00:35:36,200 --> 00:35:40,890
What should I do then, to make you sleep?

346
00:35:43,100 --> 00:35:43,900
Morn–

347
00:35:45,300 --> 00:35:46,300
–ning.
- What’s wrong?

348
00:35:58,960 --> 00:36:00,760
Lom’s sleeping.

349
00:36:00,760 --> 00:36:02,130
Let’s not wake her up.

350
00:36:02,500 --> 00:36:03,860
Why don’t we come back later?

351
00:36:04,160 --> 00:36:05,400
Let’s go. Come on.

352
00:36:05,500 --> 00:36:07,220
Hold on, shouldn’t we wake her up?

353
00:36:07,330 --> 00:36:08,130
No, leave her.

354
00:36:08,260 --> 00:36:09,810
Let’s go. Come on.

355
00:36:10,500 --> 00:36:11,500
Let’s go, Sis.

356
00:36:14,530 --> 00:36:16,680
Is it the princess or Lom who forgot where her bed is?

357
00:36:19,530 --> 00:36:21,060
Geez, Fai. What?

358
00:36:21,060 --> 00:36:22,350
Just get out first.

359
00:36:32,060 --> 00:36:35,930
Listen, why is the princess sleeping on that bed with Lom?

360
00:36:36,700 --> 00:36:40,060
Yeah, isn’t that brat afraid she’ll get her head chopped off?

361
00:36:40,460 --> 00:36:41,600
I don’t get it.

362
00:36:43,730 --> 00:36:45,640
Maybe I should go wake her up.

363
00:36:45,800 --> 00:36:48,720
Calm down, Sis! Easy there.

364
00:36:49,680 --> 00:36:52,100
There are some things you don't need to understand.

365
00:36:54,220 --> 00:36:58,100
Fai, that’s the princess of Madelin we’re talking about.

366
00:36:58,800 --> 00:37:03,560
Look, if you don’t say it, and I don’t say it–then who’d know?

367
00:37:03,680 --> 00:37:06,300
Even the nurses don’t know who Miss Blew is.

368
00:37:07,500 --> 00:37:09,730
But I don’t want Lom to regret it later.

369
00:37:11,130 --> 00:37:13,000
Leave that for the future to decide.

370
00:37:13,600 --> 00:37:17,160
For now, let’s go ask the doctor how long Lom has to stay here.

371
00:37:18,800 --> 00:37:19,860
Come on. Let’s go.

372
00:37:20,530 --> 00:37:23,680
But that’s the princess! I’m worried for Lom.

373
00:37:23,680 --> 00:37:24,680
Yeah, so what?

374
00:37:31,140 --> 00:37:34,270
Your food and medicine are ready.

375
00:37:39,600 --> 00:37:40,970
My heart skipped a beat there.

376
00:37:41,850 --> 00:37:43,970
Your food and medicine are here.

377
00:37:43,970 --> 00:37:45,310
Sorry for interrupting.

378
00:37:45,560 --> 00:37:46,500
Please excuse me.

379
00:37:56,760 --> 00:37:58,350
Let me help you with it.

380
00:38:06,460 --> 00:38:07,640
I’m sorry.

381
00:38:23,600 --> 00:38:25,520
It’s okay. I can do it.

382
00:38:25,960 --> 00:38:30,180
But I want to. Just think of me as Phatpha then.

383
00:38:31,360 --> 00:38:34,720
We’re not on an island anymore. There’s no more Wind and Phatpha.

384
00:38:35,700 --> 00:38:37,720
I miss those times together.

385
00:38:39,500 --> 00:38:40,560
Me too.

386
00:39:00,130 --> 00:39:03,020
Hello, children. Let’s learn some English today.

387
00:39:07,600 --> 00:39:11,430
This is called ‘Laughing’.

388
00:39:19,130 --> 00:39:21,260
Everything will be over soon.

389
00:39:23,160 --> 00:39:28,720
When that time comes, I’ll be the one to take you back to Madelin myself.

390
00:39:55,800 --> 00:39:58,530
Let’s eat, Wind, so you can take the medicine.

391
00:40:08,800 --> 00:40:09,970
Want some more?

392
00:40:11,500 --> 00:40:12,360
It’s delicious.

393
00:40:13,060 --> 00:40:14,300
Then, eat up.

394
00:40:20,970 --> 00:40:22,350
Have some more.

395
00:40:33,700 --> 00:40:35,060
You got something on your face.

396
00:40:39,960 --> 00:40:43,100
Good morn–

397
00:40:48,800 --> 00:40:53,260
Lom. Miss Blew. Are you two all right?

398
00:40:56,560 --> 00:40:58,520
Miss Vayo and I are fine.

399
00:41:07,860 --> 00:41:11,270
I’d better leave then so that you siblings can talk.

400
00:41:12,130 --> 00:41:14,390
Does anyone want to feed her for me?

401
00:41:15,850 --> 00:41:17,060
I do!

402
00:41:18,890 --> 00:41:21,140
No need. I can do it myself.

403
00:41:22,140 --> 00:41:23,970
But I want to do it.

404
00:41:31,130 --> 00:41:32,770
She’s all yours then, Miss Fai.

405
00:41:33,200 --> 00:41:34,000
No problem.

406
00:41:45,600 --> 00:41:49,460
Aww, don’t look so sad.

407
00:41:50,100 --> 00:41:54,100
Here, let me do the honour.

408
00:41:54,460 --> 00:41:55,680
It’s just plain rice.

409
00:41:55,760 --> 00:41:57,310
Open your mouth.

410
00:42:00,180 --> 00:42:01,970
Good girl.

411
00:42:02,330 --> 00:42:03,500
It’s horrible.

412
00:42:06,000 --> 00:42:08,730
Not as sweet as those bites you took earlier, huh?

413
00:42:10,300 --> 00:42:11,860
I’d rather help myself.

414
00:42:15,460 --> 00:42:18,330
So, you can use your hands now?

415
00:42:22,400 --> 00:42:24,100
Come, Lil Sis.

416
00:42:24,100 --> 00:42:24,930
What?

417
00:42:24,960 --> 00:42:25,700
Let me feed you.

418
00:42:25,700 --> 00:42:27,060
It’s okay. I’m good.

419
00:42:27,360 --> 00:42:28,060
Come on.

420
00:42:28,060 --> 00:42:29,970
No, I’m good here.

421
00:42:30,460 --> 00:42:32,180
- No.
- Come on. Be a good boy.

422
00:42:32,180 --> 00:42:33,350
No good boy.

423
00:42:33,660 --> 00:42:35,100
- Come on, good boy. Eat it.
- No.

424
00:42:46,530 --> 00:42:50,100
[Vayo]: We’re not on an island anymore. There’s no more Wind and Phatpha.

425
00:42:51,200 --> 00:42:53,270
[Blew]: I miss those times together.

426
00:42:54,060 --> 00:42:55,130
[Vayo]: Me too.

427
00:43:07,130 --> 00:43:08,160
Miss Blew.

428
00:43:14,360 --> 00:43:16,700
Have you just arrived, Miss Lada, Miss Rose?

429
00:43:18,200 --> 00:43:22,330
Yes, Lada and I went to get some snacks first.

430
00:43:27,130 --> 00:43:30,390
Miss Din and Miss Nam are talking to Lom inside.

431
00:43:33,400 --> 00:43:37,060
Then, let the siblings have some alone time together.

432
00:43:57,660 --> 00:44:00,640
Looks like something is bothering your mind, Miss Blew.

433
00:44:01,760 --> 00:44:04,310
Lada and I are always here if you need someone to talk to.

434
00:44:04,360 --> 00:44:06,100
We’re more than happy to help.

435
00:44:07,530 --> 00:44:11,770
Don’t worry if it’s something private. Your secret will be safe with us.

436
00:44:11,900 --> 00:44:13,930
We promise we’ll keep our lips sealed.

437
00:44:21,700 --> 00:44:30,360
In your opinion, what do you think love is?

438
00:44:35,000 --> 00:44:42,350
Love, for me, is staying by each other’s side–complimenting each other,

439
00:44:42,350 --> 00:44:44,600
protecting and caring for each other–

440
00:44:45,270 --> 00:44:48,770
and be each other’s happiness on a simply ordinary day.

441
00:44:49,180 --> 00:44:52,270
For me, that person is Din.

442
00:44:55,270 --> 00:45:02,680
As for me, a good love is something that makes you love yourself.

443
00:45:03,700 --> 00:45:08,600
I used to think I could live alone and be on my own.

444
00:45:09,930 --> 00:45:18,640
But after I met Nam, I’ve realised that we don’t always need to be strong or good at everything.

445
00:45:19,500 --> 00:45:22,300
If there are times when I want to cry or don’t want to act strong,

446
00:45:22,960 --> 00:45:25,760
Nam will always be there to support me.

447
00:45:28,560 --> 00:45:31,530
What about you, Miss Blew?

448
00:45:35,900 --> 00:45:37,100
I don’t know.

449
00:45:38,930 --> 00:45:40,560
I’ve never been in love before.

450
00:45:42,260 --> 00:45:46,970
The only love I’ve experienced is one that I have for my people in Madelin.

451
00:45:51,130 --> 00:45:55,560
All this time, I’ve only focused on my duty as a princess.

452
00:45:56,970 --> 00:46:06,640
So, I have no idea how it feels when you’re in love.

453
00:46:12,200 --> 00:46:17,520
Please don’t worry. When love comes to you, you’ll just know it.

454
00:46:43,730 --> 00:46:45,330
Excuse me, are you Miss Fah?

455
00:46:48,560 --> 00:46:50,600
Hello. Have a seat, please.

456
00:46:54,960 --> 00:46:58,680
I’m Sebastian, Prince Karel’s friend.

457
00:46:58,680 --> 00:47:01,350
I heard Princess Blew has sent you.

458
00:47:02,200 --> 00:47:04,520
I’m Fah, a reporter from Thailand.

459
00:47:06,960 --> 00:47:11,350
The princess wants me to hand deliver a confidential letter to the prince.

460
00:47:12,600 --> 00:47:14,430
How should I trust you?

461
00:47:20,300 --> 00:47:22,270
Is this enough for a proof?

462
00:47:30,330 --> 00:47:33,640
Hello, Sebastian. It’s Princess Blew here.

463
00:47:33,640 --> 00:47:38,600
Fah is our person, and I need you to trust everything that she has to say.

464
00:47:38,970 --> 00:47:41,060
I have a favour to ask you.

465
00:47:41,060 --> 00:47:43,850
Please contact Karel secretly.

466
00:47:43,850 --> 00:47:45,560
Thank you very much.

467
00:47:58,000 --> 00:47:59,960
The prince is on his way to France.

468
00:48:01,860 --> 00:48:02,660
Really?

469
00:48:04,660 --> 00:48:06,660
I’ll let you know when he arrives.

470
00:48:08,160 --> 00:48:09,130
Thank you so much.

471
00:48:09,760 --> 00:48:11,720
I’ll report this back to Thailand.

472
00:48:11,760 --> 00:48:13,640
The princess will be so happy to hear it.

473
00:48:14,930 --> 00:48:17,800
I’d appreciate it if you'd only keep this to yourself.

474
00:49:40,930 --> 00:49:42,060
Is it far?

475
00:49:44,660 --> 00:49:47,270
Just cross this mountain and we’ll reach the border of Thailand.

476
00:49:49,000 --> 00:49:51,140
I didn’t expect you to come by yourself, sir.

477
00:49:51,960 --> 00:49:56,270
If it weren’t because of those muppets, I wouldn’t have had to be here myself.

478
00:49:57,600 --> 00:50:00,500
The weapons I’ve asked you to prepare, have you got all of them?

479
00:50:02,100 --> 00:50:03,180
Yes, sir.

480
00:50:31,600 --> 00:50:32,430
Dad.

481
00:50:41,800 --> 00:50:43,100
How are you feeling?

482
00:50:43,730 --> 00:50:44,850
Much better now.

483
00:50:45,100 --> 00:50:46,930
The doctor will let know when to be discharged.

484
00:50:48,700 --> 00:50:49,770
Where’s the princess?

485
00:50:50,700 --> 00:50:51,600
In a shower.

486
00:50:57,400 --> 00:50:59,430
What’s the matter, Dad?

487
00:51:01,600 --> 00:51:05,730
Those thugs we executed on the island are all Thai.

488
00:51:08,760 --> 00:51:11,970
They were probably hired.

489
00:51:12,350 --> 00:51:16,600
I already have my team look into it if there are any more of them.

490
00:51:16,960 --> 00:51:17,720
That’s why I want to–

491
00:51:17,720 --> 00:51:23,970
Have you ever wondered why they were so quick to track down Miss Blew and my whereabouts?

492
00:51:26,330 --> 00:51:27,600
What do you mean?

493
00:51:51,600 --> 00:51:52,400
Hold on.

494
00:52:00,560 --> 00:52:02,300
Nothing. Thank you.

495
00:54:08,460 --> 00:54:13,700
It’s me. Just hide in here first. I’ll take care of the rest.

496
00:54:29,300 --> 00:54:31,100
Chief!

497
00:54:35,160 --> 00:54:35,960
Don’t worry about me.

498
00:54:37,260 --> 00:54:38,100
He went that way.

499
00:54:38,360 --> 00:54:39,260
Go after him!

500
00:54:39,800 --> 00:54:40,600
Quick!

501
00:54:41,500 --> 00:54:42,300
Go!

502
00:55:01,360 --> 00:55:02,560
It’s all clear.

503
00:55:02,960 --> 00:55:04,730
How did the cops know I’ll be here?

504
00:55:05,800 --> 00:55:06,600
No idea.

505
00:55:07,800 --> 00:55:14,640
But right now, you have to get out of here before Wathit will send his men to secure all the exits.

506
00:55:15,530 --> 00:55:16,800
Let me make this clear.

507
00:55:17,660 --> 00:55:20,930
If I don’t make it out of here, you won’t either.

508
00:55:54,100 --> 00:55:59,640
Have you ever wondered why they were so quick to track down Miss Blew and my whereabouts?

509
00:55:59,860 --> 00:56:00,760
What do you mean?

510
00:56:01,160 --> 00:56:03,850
Is Chief Santi on your team too, Dad?

511
00:56:04,160 --> 00:56:08,520
Are you saying Santi is working with them?

512
00:56:09,130 --> 00:56:11,220
We can’t trust anyone right now.

513
00:56:11,260 --> 00:56:13,810
The traitors have some of their men disguised among us cops.

514
00:56:14,000 --> 00:56:16,640
I got summoned to the hotel immediately.

515
00:56:16,660 --> 00:56:18,640
Take care of the princess for me.

516
00:56:18,760 --> 00:56:20,100
No one told me anything.

517
00:56:20,400 --> 00:56:21,930
Did Chief tell you to go?

518
00:56:22,530 --> 00:56:23,850
Nothing. I’m hanging up.

519
00:56:24,530 --> 00:56:26,600
It’s not that I don’t trust Dad, Din.

520
00:56:26,600 --> 00:56:31,850
But it’s those around him–whether the cops or his men–I don’t trust any of them.

521
00:56:33,660 --> 00:56:35,330
We got ambushed, sir!

522
00:56:36,800 --> 00:56:39,160
They’ve followed us here like you said, Uncle Thit.

523
00:56:39,660 --> 00:56:41,600
I’ll send my team to standby on the island.

524
00:56:42,530 --> 00:56:44,130
Those thugs will definitely show up there tomorrow.

525
00:56:44,400 --> 00:56:45,810
Can you put my team on the line?

526
00:56:45,810 --> 00:56:46,720
Hang on.

527
00:56:51,300 --> 00:56:52,310
Yes, sir.

528
00:56:55,360 --> 00:57:00,430
Just as I thought, it’s really you, Chief. You only have two choices.

529
00:57:01,060 --> 00:57:05,020
Help us or walk straight to jail.

530
00:57:21,760 --> 00:57:23,530
Nam, is everything okay?

531
00:57:24,930 --> 00:57:27,060
Lucky we’ve moved Miss Blew out in time.

532
00:57:27,700 --> 00:57:29,180
Did they catch the suspect?

533
00:57:30,160 --> 00:57:32,130
No, he got away.

534
00:57:33,560 --> 00:57:38,720
But Uncle Thit already has his men check the security footage from every road leaving Surat Thani.

535
00:57:48,300 --> 00:57:49,960
Nothing. Thank you.

536
00:58:22,960 --> 00:58:24,430
Just a moment, Your Highness.

537
00:58:33,660 --> 00:58:35,660
The car is coming to take you to the safehouse in Khao Yai.

538
00:58:36,960 --> 00:58:37,760
Thank you.

539
00:58:38,760 --> 00:58:41,970
Here, Fai packed these clothes for you.

540
00:58:42,300 --> 00:58:43,600
I’ll keep you posted on any update.

541
00:58:50,100 --> 00:58:51,100
That’s your car.

542
00:58:55,060 --> 00:58:56,770
This one?

543
00:58:57,700 --> 00:59:02,390
Yes, Your Highness–to avoid getting attention from the suspects.

544
00:59:05,560 --> 00:59:07,270
A rescue wagon, huh?

545
00:59:10,100 --> 00:59:12,140
At least, there’s no dead body in there.

546
00:59:13,330 --> 00:59:14,730
Does that mean there was earlier?

547
00:59:17,360 --> 00:59:18,680
I’m not sure.

548
00:59:21,560 --> 00:59:24,270
Let’s hurry. Please, Your Highness.

549
00:59:25,060 --> 00:59:26,100
Let's go.

550
00:59:48,760 --> 00:59:49,890
We’re here.

551
00:59:52,130 --> 00:59:54,260
Can’t believe there’s a house hidden deep in the forest.

552
00:59:55,700 --> 01:00:01,310
We have no phone signal here. If there’s anything, the staff at the resort will light the SOS flare to let us know immediately.

553
01:00:02,060 --> 01:00:03,310
Let’s go in.

554
01:00:22,730 --> 01:00:24,400
Any news about that cop?

555
01:00:25,530 --> 01:00:30,310
We’re working on it but General Wathit is watching our every move.

556
01:00:31,500 --> 01:00:33,100
It’ll probably take a while.

557
01:00:33,530 --> 01:00:35,020
I don’t want to risk it.

558
01:00:42,100 --> 01:00:44,310
It’s double the amount you got last time.

559
01:00:44,800 --> 01:00:46,330
Just give me Vayo’s whereabouts.

560
01:00:49,660 --> 01:00:51,100
You have three days.

561
01:01:06,560 --> 01:01:07,730
I’ll be in touch.

562
01:01:32,200 --> 01:01:33,660
Is it okay?

563
01:01:34,700 --> 01:01:36,060
Of course, no problem.

564
01:01:37,400 --> 01:01:39,430
Then, please get some rest.

565
01:01:39,430 --> 01:01:41,720
I’ll go fix something for you to eat. I’ll let you know when it’s done.

566
01:01:43,330 --> 01:01:44,520
Miss Vayo.

567
01:01:45,560 --> 01:01:46,360
Yes?

568
01:01:48,200 --> 01:01:49,560
I have a question.

569
01:01:50,500 --> 01:01:51,300
Okay.

570
01:01:52,700 --> 01:01:55,640
Promise me first that you won’t lie.

571
01:01:57,730 --> 01:01:59,560
Okay, I promise.

572
01:02:03,460 --> 01:02:05,500
Bua told me that the woman you like is me.

573
01:02:10,700 --> 01:02:11,640
Well…

574
01:02:11,640 --> 01:02:15,390
But I’ll never believe it until I’d hear it from you.

575
01:02:18,360 --> 01:02:21,680
Why are you asking me all of a sudden?

576
01:02:24,600 --> 01:02:26,640
How do you feel about me?

577
01:02:32,260 --> 01:02:33,560
I…

578
01:02:35,350 --> 01:02:39,890
If you think my question is inappropriate, please forget it.

579
01:02:48,660 --> 01:02:50,000
That’s not what I think, Miss Blew.

580
01:02:56,060 --> 01:02:58,700
It’s because I don’t just ‘like’ you.

581
01:03:01,760 --> 01:03:02,660
What do you mean?

582
01:03:16,660 --> 01:03:21,970
It might seem too soon for me to say it since we just got to know each other.

583
01:03:24,600 --> 01:03:27,100
But I have absolutely no doubt about how I feel.

584
01:03:29,600 --> 01:03:31,560
And how do you feel?

585
01:03:41,700 --> 01:03:46,140
Please forgive me for not knowing my own place.

586
01:03:46,810 --> 01:03:50,600
All this time, I keep telling myself how I don’t deserve to be with you.

587
01:03:51,100 --> 01:03:57,100
But whenever you’re near, I just can’t help falling deeper and deeper.

588
01:04:00,960 --> 01:04:02,560
I love you, Miss Blew.

589
01:04:11,460 --> 01:04:14,140
How many loves have you had before?

590
01:04:17,520 --> 01:04:18,890
Yes?

591
01:04:21,660 --> 01:04:25,640
You have dated many girls in the past.

592
01:04:26,460 --> 01:04:30,560
All these situations might have brought us to get close to each other.

593
01:04:33,100 --> 01:04:35,970
So, I just want you to be sure…

594
01:04:36,970 --> 01:04:41,640
whether this is love…or just a crush.

595
01:04:45,300 --> 01:04:46,810
I am sure.

596
01:04:50,000 --> 01:04:51,850
I am sure that this is love.

597
01:05:13,060 --> 01:05:18,270
I genuinely appreciate how you feel about me.

598
01:05:21,060 --> 01:05:23,560
But I’m afraid I can’t return the feelings.

599
01:06:06,000 --> 01:06:11,310
I genuinely appreciate how you feel about me.

600
01:06:14,000 --> 01:06:16,640
But I’m afraid I can’t return the feelings.

601
01:06:25,600 --> 01:06:32,350
Knowing what I just said didn’t make you feel upset or disdain, I’m already content enough.

602
01:06:36,000 --> 01:06:41,140
To me, you’ll always be my last love–

603
01:06:48,260 --> 01:06:50,960
whether it’ll come true or not.

604
01:07:40,460 --> 01:07:44,100
Are we going back to Madelin after we finish here?

605
01:07:44,160 --> 01:07:49,220
Not yet. We’ll go back to Thailand to get rid of the real princess.

606
01:07:50,260 --> 01:07:53,180
Hasn’t Henri already taken care of that? Why do we have to go?

607
01:07:54,500 --> 01:07:55,960
I don’t trust him.

608
01:07:56,730 --> 01:07:59,310
He has no resentment towards the royal family.

609
01:08:00,060 --> 01:08:05,970
If he changes his mind to be on the princess’s side, my plan to take revenge will just go down the drain.

610
01:08:09,930 --> 01:08:12,310
What grudges are you holding against the royal family?

611
01:08:15,060 --> 01:08:16,600
It’s none of your business.

612
01:08:17,660 --> 01:08:20,350
Just do your best as a fake princess.

613
01:08:33,729 --> 01:08:37,000
[Next Episode]
Dad will lure Henri here and arrest all of them.

614
01:08:40,640 --> 01:08:42,060
Miss Vayo!

615
01:08:42,930 --> 01:08:44,520
Is Miss Blew okay?

616
01:08:45,130 --> 01:08:47,020
They’ve taken Miss Blew.

617
01:08:47,529 --> 01:08:50,100
- Uncle Thit and his team are–
- I’ll go help her.

618
01:08:51,460 --> 01:08:53,930
You and Karel will come to Thailand, Father?

619
01:08:54,000 --> 01:08:58,970
We should be able to get some family time together before you’ll come back to take your throne as the Queen.

620
01:08:59,000 --> 01:09:01,060
This is not what we’ve planned, Grace.

621
01:09:01,300 --> 01:09:03,720
What if my father and King Arther already find out?

622
01:09:03,729 --> 01:09:05,720
Wouldn’t we all get a death sentence?

623
01:09:06,800 --> 01:09:08,640
You look exactly like me.

624
01:09:38,350 --> 01:09:48,770
♫ I wonder which star it is that guided me to meet you ♫

625
01:09:50,350 --> 01:10:01,390
♫Or is it destiny that has brought us together♫

626
01:10:01,890 --> 01:10:07,890
♫You’re like the wind, carrying me to the sky♫

627
01:10:07,890 --> 01:10:12,890
♫No matter how high, I won’t be afraid♫

628
01:10:12,890 --> 01:10:18,680
♫ Only you is enough, I don’t need anything else ♫

629
01:10:18,680 --> 01:10:27,520
♫ust us together is enough, you’re the meaning in my life♫

630
01:10:27,520 --> 01:10:34,680
♫Every day from now, please stay by my side♫

631
01:10:35,020 --> 01:10:37,140
[Desires in the Wind]
♫and we’ll always have each other♫

632
01:10:37,140 --> 01:10:40,430
[North Star Entertainment]
♫and we’ll always have each other♫

